GENERAL MOTORS CORPORATION, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. PREFERRED ELECTRIC & WIRE CORPORATION, Defendant-Appellee. No. 289. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 15, 1937. Drury W. Cooper, and Thomas J. Byrne, both of New York City, and Harry W. Lindsey, Jr., of Chicago, 111., for appellant. Theodore S. Kenyon, John L. Lotsch, and W. Houston Kenyon, Jr., all of New York City, for appellee.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER curiam:.

Decree affirmed.
